{"title":"3T RaceMax Gravel Bike Combines Integrale Upgrade at Lower Prices & New WPNT Colors","link":"https://bikerumor.com/3t-racemax-gravel-bike-combines-integrale-upgrade-at-lower-prices-new-wpnt-colors/","date":1731427200000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_no-more-pesky-cables-1536x1024.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"3T RaceMax WPNT Integrale aero carbon gravel bike gets integrated, finally free of toptube cable routing\" /></p>\n<p>Highlighting their new painted-in-Italy WPNT colors inspired by classic car paintjobs, 3T almost glossed over a really big update to their core RaceMax gravel bike… an Integrale shift finally gives the bike fully internal cable routing. Sure, 3T already adopted fully internal routing on their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-3t-strada-aero-road-bike-integrates-internal-routing/\" target=\"_blank\">aero road bike</a> a couple of years ago, and then incrementally on each of their premium made-in-Italy Italia models since. But now, the more affordable standard 3T RaceMax WPNT Integrale drops the annoying toptube routing port. And it’s also available as a frameset for 1/2 the cost of the Italia edition!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3T RaceMax WPNT Integrale carbon gravel bike is integrated!</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-jpg.webp\"><img width=\"2400\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-jpg.webp\" alt=\"3T RaceMax WPNT Integrale aero carbon gravel bike gets integrated, new colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-jpg.webp 2400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_new-color-options-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/3T)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For four years, the 3T RaceMax has been 3T’s best-selling gravel bike – aerodynamic, versatile with faster and wide 700c tires or even wider 650b tires for bigger adventures, and plenty of mounts for bikepacking and adventure. Now, 3T gives the RaceMax a “fresh coat of paint” by adding it to their new WPNT program, with 5 special edition metallic &amp; iridescent colors said to be inspired by classic cars. That “We Paint” label meaning that 3T paints the bikes themselves in Italy, letting them run more special edition colors. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-jpg.webp\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-jpg.webp\" alt=\"3T RaceMax WPNT Integrale aero carbon gravel bike gets integrated, clean cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-jpg.webp 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/3T-RaceMax-WPNT-Integrale-aero-carbon-gravel-bike-gets-integrated_up-close-768x576.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At the same time, the 3T RaceMax WPNT also becomes “Integrale” like their top-tier made-in-Italy Italia edition carbon road &amp; gravel bikes…</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Why does an integrated gravel bike update matter?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs.jpg\"><img width=\"600\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-600x450.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-600x450.jpg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-80x60.jpg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/3T-Exploro-650b-WTB-Horizon-47mm-tire_Restrap-bikepacking-packs-265x198.jpg 265w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-c